.TH "mtd_pairing_groups" 9 "mtd_pairing_groups" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mtd_pairing_groups \- get the number of pairing groups
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mtd_pairing_groups
.BI "(struct mtd_info *mtd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mtd" 12
pointer to new MTD device info structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the number of pairing groups.

This number is usually equal to the number of bits exposed by a single
cell, and can be used in conjunction with \fBmtd_pairing_info_to_wunit\fP
to iterate over all pages of a given pair.
